BEST WAY (Industry standard): Nginx + SSL (Let’s Encrypt)
🔥 Goal

You want this:

Frontend: https://onebusinessindia.com
API:      https://onebusinessindia.com/api
Backend:  http://localhost:3001 (hidden)
✅ STEP 1: Install Nginx (if not installed)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx -y

Check:

sudo systemctl status nginx
✅ STEP 2: Point domain to VPS

Make sure DNS is:

A record:
onebusinessindia.com → YOUR_VPS_IP
www.onebusinessindia.com → YOUR_VPS_IP
✅ STEP 3: Install SSL (Certbot)

Install Certbot:

sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y

Now run:

sudo certbot --nginx -d onebusinessindia.com -d www.onebusinessindia.com

👉 It will:

Automatically enable HTTPS
Install SSL certificate
Redirect HTTP → HTTPS
✅ STEP 4: Configure Nginx reverse proxy

Edit config:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default

Replace with:

server {
    server_name onebusinessindia.com www.onebusinessindia.com;

    root /var/www/html;  # your React build folder

    index index.html;

    # Frontend (React)
    location / {
        try_files $uri /index.html;
    }

    # Backend API
    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    }
}
✅ STEP 5: Restart Nginx
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl restart nginx
✅ STEP 6: Run backend locally (IMPORTANT)

Your backend should run like:

node server.js

or using PM2:

pm2 start server.js --name backend
pm2 save

It should listen on:

http://127.0.0.1:3001

NOT public IP.

🎯 FINAL RESULT

Now your API becomes:

https://onebusinessindia.com/api/v1/public/articles

✔ Secure (HTTPS)
✔ No mixed content error
✔ No IP exposure
✔ Production ready